sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J70590
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
S04432 is in pSB1AC3, J70554 is in pSB1AC3; thus J70590 will probably be in pSB1AK3
the goal is to see if the BioScaffold can be replaced with an internal GSGSGS fusion,
also will replace with a dead fusion
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Julie Norville
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance:
BioBrick assembly, to add GSGSGS fusion add following annealed oligos:
J70556-fi
J70556-ric
To add a dead fusion (i.e. a stop codon), add the following annealed oligo nucleotides:
deadfusion J70556d-fi
deadfusion J70556d-ri
